This paper is about neural generative models for text generation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses variational autoencoders, which are a type of deep learning model, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates the models using various metrics, which involves statistical analysis, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions reconstructions, which could involve image processing, so cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely but still possible sub-category.
